# Rayos Convex Guardrails

- Enforce authentication and tenant/organization checks in all public functions.
- Validate all public args and return predictable typed results.
- Keep query/mutation/action wrappers thin; move logic into reusable TypeScript helpers.
- Use indexes over broad filtering for production query paths.
- Avoid cache-breaking patterns in queries (for example time-based non-determinism).
- Prefer clear, user-safe errors for expected failures and throw for exceptional cases.
